  "text": "So far we have assumed that the parity-preserving part is described by general relativity. If one generalizes this part to the Horndeski-type Lagrangian [CITATION_1] , ν A and c A T are also affected by this modification. However, the two effects cannot be canceled out because the parityviolating modification depends on λ A and the wave number, while the Horndeski-type modification does not. The two ways of modifying gravity are thus distinct, and therefore the above statements are robust.",
